definitions.definition: Characterized by exceptionally early development or maturity .
examples: The precocious plant was already blooming flowers by day 4.

definitions.definition: Exhibiting advanced skills and aptitudes at an abnormally early age.
examples: The precocious child began reading the newspaper at age four.

main_definition: Characterized by exceptionally early development or maturity .
secondary_definitions: Exhibiting advanced skills and aptitudes at an abnormally early age.
